  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Joseph Lupton is worried because the box sent by William Lloyd Garrison from Leeds has not arrived. The ladies are much disappointed, but they have nevertheless again collected a few contributions for the bazaar and have sent a box directed to Maria Weston Chapman. The box also contains 4 pounds in gold wrapped in paper, and a parcel for Frederick Douglass from Miss Holland, etc. The ladies want to know if the articles in the box are suitable. They also want to know if Maria W. Chapman&apos;s purpose could not be better served by their selling a few smaller articles in England and then sending the proceeds. The 4 pounds that are enclosed were chiefly raised in this way.</subfield>
